President Trump addressed the recent terrorist attack in New York City, expressing condolences for the victims and vowing to investigate the attacker and his connections. He also announced his intention to terminate the Diversity Visa Lottery program and called for a merit-based immigration system. Trump emphasized the need for stronger and quicker justice for terrorists and criticized the current trade deals of the United States, stating that his administration is renegotiating them. He also discussed the upcoming tax cuts and tax reform plan, which he described as the largest in the country's history. Trump mentioned the appointment of a new head of the Federal Reserve and his upcoming trip to Asia. He highlighted the progress his administration has made in appointing federal judges and mentioned the possibility of sending the New York attacker to Guantanamo Bay.